'''Francisco Jose Blanco''' is a [[structural biology|structural biologist]] working as Group Leader at the Centro de investigación Cooperativa en biociencias CIC bioGUNE, Biscay, Spain.  His research utilizes [[protein NMR|Nuclear Magnetic Resonance spectroscopy]] to characterize [[protein structure]] and [[protein folding]]. His major contributions to the field of [[protein folding]] include the study of the formation and stability of isolated [[beta hairpin|β-hairpin]] structures,<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Blanco FJ, Rivas G, Serrano L |title=A short linear peptide that folds into a native stable beta-hairpin |journal=Nature Structural Biology |volume=1 |issue=9 |pages=584–90 |date=September 1994 |pmid=7634098 |doi=10.1038/nsb0994-584 }}</ref> and the analysis of the folding pathway of the SH3 domain from the α-spectrin protein.<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Blanco FJ, Serrano L, Forman-Kay JD |title=High populations of non-native structures in the denatured state are compatible with the formation of the native folded state |journal=Journal of Molecular Biology |volume=284 |issue=4 |pages=1153–64 |date=December 1998 |pmid=9837733 |doi=10.1006/jmbi.1998.2229}}</ref> His 68 structural biology papers listed in [[Web of Science]] have been cited over 2500 times, giving him an [[h-index]] of 27.

