{{Anthropology of kinship}}

A '''lineage''' is an [[unilineal descent]] group that can demonstrate their common descent from a known [[Most recent common ancestor|apical ancestor]]. Unilineal lineages can be matrilineal or patrilineal, depending on whether they are traced through mothers or fathers, respectively. Whether matrilineal or patrilineal descent is considered most significant differs from culture to culture.

