An '''ochrea''' ([[Latin language|Latin]] ''ocrea'', [[greave]] or protective legging), also spelled '''ocrea''', is a plant structure formed of [[stipule]]s fused into a sheath surrounding the stem, and is typically found in the [[Polygonaceae]]. 

In [[Arecaceae|palms]] it denotes an extension of the leaf sheath beyond the [[Petiole (botany)|petiole]] insertion.

